data.title: East Coast Cereal Found its way to Yakima
data.meta_description: This breakfast cereal isn't common to the pacific northwest.
data.text:
Grocery Outlet has a Unique Cereal to the Pacific Northwest

I love walking down the aisles of our local Grocery Outlet stores. I never have any intended reason to buy anything, but I'll just stroll through and see what falls in the cart. So many times I'll find items that I can't find at any other store in Yakima. Me, I'm a huge fan of breakfast cereal and seeing this made me smile out loud.

You might walk by this and think it's a generic-type of cereal. Not from the major companies like Kellogg's or General Mills but this particular cereal is even more unique as it's not commonly found in the pacific northwest. This company that sometimes supplies grocery stores on the east coast found its way over to Yakima of all places and I'm so happy it did as it's not a knock-off of any other popular cereal on the market.

PB & J cereal is just that. Peanut butter puffs (think Peanut Butter Crunch) along with other puffs flavored like strawberry. It's a unique combination but super good and so happy I found it at Grocery Outlet. This photo was taken at the location on Summitview but the other locations may or may not have it. If you're in for a treat, might swing by and grab a box or two.
